Foundational crate shared across CTX tools (ctx-scan, ctx-context, ctx-brief, ctx-status); home to definitions that must stay synchronized to prevent silent bugs.

The `access` module is the single source of truth for the secret/binary denylist — a divergent copy is a secret-exfiltration risk (ADR-023). The `hashtree` module defines the content-hash sidecar schema parsed by both ctx-scan (generator) and ctx-context (server); hashes recorded by one must be comparable by the other. The `status_table` module parses and escapes the `docs/STATUS.md` table model shared by ctx-brief (matching requests) and ctx-status (migrating/rendering); a single parser/escaper prevents drift. Each consumer tool maps the neutral results here into its own typed error, but the core logic is never copied.